<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-20T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.151/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-20T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 20,
                                        1925—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 20—9:14
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>389. Your 278, July 18, 2 p.m.<note n="7" xml:id="d244fn7">Not
                                printed.</note> The French Government last week officially but
                            orally informed the Greek Chargé d’Affaires that it consented to the
                            waterworks loan subject to the priority of the Greek share of the
                            Ottoman public debt.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>